                            <comment id="83399" author="jamesanunez" created="Wed, 7 May 2014 16:09:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m seeing sanity-quota test 7a and 7b occasionally fail with the &quot;reintegration failed&quot; error; &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/91d264c4-d5cb-11e3-83eb-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/91d264c4-d5cb-11e3-83eb-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt; . Tests 7a and 7b are still set to timeout at 90 sec. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should these tests change the amount of time allowed for the reintegration as this patch does for test 7c?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="49289" author="niu" created="Mon, 17 Dec 2012 03:24:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch landed for 2.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="48721" author="niu" created="Tue, 4 Dec 2012 04:28:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4739&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4739&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="48018" author="johann" created="Mon, 19 Nov 2012 16:23:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, 90s is how long it takes to the writeback thread before restarting reintegration after a failure, so it does not sound so surprising, no?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47983" author="niu" created="Sun, 18 Nov 2012 23:33:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This might be related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2322&quot; title=&quot;ODB_IDX_READ should be allowed during recovery&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2322&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2322&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but I don&apos;t see why the reintegration for OSTs is not finished in 90s. Johann, any idea?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
